(44, 27, 21, 19, 107, 5, 6, 'not have loosed from Crete', 'Deliverance in Times of Distress', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking help in distress. In Acts, Paul warns of impending harm, while in Psalms, the people cry out to the Lord in their trouble and receive deliverance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 21, 44, 27, 7, 7, 'not have loosed from Crete', 'Paul''s Warning and Journey', 'This connection highlights Paul''s prior warning about sailing from Crete, which is referenced in both passages. In Acts 27:21, Paul reflects on the consequences of ignoring his advice after they have already faced difficulties during their journey, which began in Acts 27:7.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 21, 44, 27, 9, 10, 'ye should have hearkened unto me', 'Paul''s Warning About the Voyage', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s warning regarding the dangers of the voyage. In Acts 27:10, he predicts ''hurt and much damage,'' which is echoed in Acts 27:21 where he states they should have hearkened to him to avoid ''harm and loss.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 21, 44, 27, 33, 35, 'ye should have hearkened unto me', 'Paul''s Leadership in Crisis', 'This connection highlights Paul''s role as a leader during a crisis. In the first passage, he warns the crew about the dangers of their decisions, while in the second, he encourages them to eat for their health, demonstrating his concern for their well-being.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 22, 44, 27, 25, 25, 'be of good cheer', 'Encouragement in Adversity', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''be of good cheer,'' highlighting a shared theme of encouragement amidst challenging circumstances. The assurance of safety in the first passage is echoed in the second, reinforcing faith in God''s promises.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 22, 44, 27, 36, 36, 'be of good cheer', 'Encouragement and Cheer', 'This connection highlights the theme of encouragement, as both passages mention being ''of good cheer.'' The first passage assures safety, leading to the collective cheerfulness expressed in the second.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
