(44, 27, 23, 45, 1, 9, 9, 'whom I serve', 'Service to God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of serving God. In Acts, Paul speaks of serving God through the angel''s presence, while in Romans, he expresses his service to God in the gospel.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 23, 55, 4, 17, 17, 'the angel of God, whose I am', 'Divine Support in Adversity', 'Both passages emphasize divine presence and support during challenging times. In Acts, Paul speaks of the angel of God standing by him, while in 2 Timothy, he mentions the Lord standing with him, providing strength.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 23, 58, 1, 14, 14, 'angel of God', 'Angelic Ministry and Guidance', 'This connection highlights the role of angels as divine messengers. Both passages emphasize the presence of angels in the lives of believers, with Acts 27:23 referencing an angel of God and Hebrews 1:14 describing angels as ministering spirits.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 23, 23, 44, 21, 21, 'whom I serve', 'Servanthood and Divine Assurance', 'This connection highlights the theme of servanthood, as both passages emphasize the relationship between God and His servants. In Acts, Paul identifies himself as a servant of God, while Isaiah reminds Israel of their identity as God''s servants.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 23, 27, 6, 16, 16, 'whom I serve', 'Divine Deliverance Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of divine protection and deliverance. In Acts, Paul speaks of the angel of God, while in Daniel, the king expresses confidence that Daniel''s God will deliver him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 24, 44, 23, 11, 11, 'thou must be brought before Cesar', 'Paul''s Assurance of Witness', 'Both passages emphasize God''s assurance to Paul regarding his journey to Rome. In Acts 23:11, the Lord encourages Paul by stating he must bear witness at Rome, while Acts 27:24 reiterates that Paul must be brought before Caesar, highlighting divine protection and purpose.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 24, 55, 4, 16, 17, 'God hath given thee all them that sail with thee', 'Divine Support in Trials', 'Both passages emphasize God''s presence and support during difficult times. In Acts, God assures Paul of safety, while in 2 Timothy, Paul acknowledges the Lord''s strength despite abandonment.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 24, 40, 10, 28, 28, 'Fear not, Paul', 'Fear and Divine Protection', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear and divine assurance. In Acts, Paul is reassured not to fear because God has granted safety to those with him, while Matthew emphasizes the importance of fearing God over human threats.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 24, 1, 19, 29, 29, 'God hath given thee all them', 'Divine Protection in Crisis', 'Both passages emphasize God''s protection during perilous situations. In Acts, God assures Paul of safety for all aboard, while in Genesis, God remembers Abraham and saves Lot from destruction.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 24, 44, 9, 15, 15, 'thou must be brought before Cesar', 'Divine Assurance in Adversity', 'Both passages emphasize God''s assurance to His chosen servants. In Acts 27:24, God assures Paul of safety and purpose, while in Acts 9:15, God designates Paul as a chosen vessel for His mission.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 24, 59, 5, 16, 16, 'Fear not, Paul', 'Prayer and Divine Assurance', 'This connection highlights the importance of prayer and divine assurance in times of distress. In Acts, God assures Paul of safety, while James emphasizes the power of prayer for healing and support.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 24, 1, 12, 2, 2, 'God hath given thee all them', 'Divine Protection and Blessing', 'This connection highlights God''s promise of protection and blessing. In Acts, God assures Paul of safety and the lives of those with him, paralleling the blessing and greatness promised to Abraham in Genesis.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 27, 25, 45, 4, 20, 21, 'I believe God', 'Faith and Assurance in God', 'This connection highlights the theme of unwavering faith in God''s promises. Both passages emphasize being fully persuaded and believing that God will fulfill His word.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
